        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:16AM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 215 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
McCreanor, or near Lonoke, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Screeton...                       McCreanor...
Fredonia...                       Culler...
Hayley...                         Carlisle...
Barrettsville...                  Childers...
Hazen...                          Prairie Center...
Sisemore...                       Center Point...
Hallsville...                     Lonoke...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
